cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about neural architecture search for semantic image segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a hierarchical search space and uses gradient-based architecture search, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves formulating the search space and developing a specific architecture for the task, which are related to artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, which are related to multimedia. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
